solution.p:
Let's list the information about this interval as follows.

	 \amp x_i = 0\ \text{(setting the initial position at the origin);}
	 \amp v_{ix} = 0\ \text{  (initially at rest);}
	 \amp a_x = 0.5 \text{ m/s}^2\ \text{  (constant x-acceleration during this interval);}
	 \amp \text{Set t = 0 at the beginning of the interval so that we can use the standard formulas.} 
 	 \amp t = 1 \text{ s} \ \text{  (duration of this interval);}

With this information, we need to find x and v, the position and velocity at the end of interval.

	 \amp  v_x  = v_{ix} + a_x t = 0 + 0.5\times 1 = 0.5 \text{ m/s};
	 \amp  x = x_i + v_{ix} t + \frac{1}{2}a_xt^2 
	 \amp = 0 + 0 + \frac{1}{2}\times 0.5\times 1^2  = 0.25 \text{ m}.
